&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_ur=
l=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9mb3J0dW5lLmNvbS8yMDI2LzAxLzA5L2dlbi16LWNvbGxlZ2Utc3R1ZGVudHM=
tc3RydWdnbGluZy10by1yZWFkLXByb2Zlc3NvcnMtZm9yY2VkLXRvLXJldGhpbmstc3RhbmRhcm=
RzLXdhcm4tb2YtYW54aWV0eS1sYWNrLW9mLXdvcmtwbGFjZS1wcmVwYXJkbmVzcy8&amp;email=
_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decor=
ation: underline;">Jessica Hooten Wilson</a></p>=0A=
</div>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">When it comes to readi=
ng, there is something of a moral panic afoot. In the United States, high-s=
chool reading scores are tanking =E2=80=A6 and everyone seems to know why.<=
/p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Raised on a diet of in=
ternet slop, today=E2=80=99s kids think that =E2=80=98reading=E2=80=99 mean=
s scanning the captions of a Tik Tok video. For them, books are becoming in=
comprehensible relics of a <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfr=
omthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3Da5900d06a080216d=
5fb662e945e6f92a0af5236d00d589777bedc1a98c53b80d&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&am=
p;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signa=
ture=3Df0ef724bc8b59db046f2ce9f33da1002&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_=
email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9qbWFycmlvdHQuc3Vic3Rh=
Y2suY29tL3AvdGhlLWRhd24tb2YtdGhlLXBvc3QtbGl0ZXJhdGUtc29jaWV0eS1hYTE&amp;ema=
il_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-dec=
oration: underline;">waning literate age</a>. In short, literacy is being m=
urdered, and the killer is the smartphone in every child=E2=80=99s hand.</p=
>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Or is it?</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In this essay, I explo=
re a different story about why kids are becoming less literate. It=E2=80=99=
s not a story about kids getting dumbed down by an addictive new technology=
. It=E2=80=99s a story about how adults decided to <em>not</em> teach kids =
how to use a piece of very old technology.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Let me set the stage w=
ith a brief parable.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;"><img src=3D"https://ec=
onomicsfromthetopdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/divider.png" width=3D"=
120" style=3D"border: none; -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; max-width: 100=
%; margin-bottom: 24px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: au=
to;"></p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Several millennia ago,=
 humans <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?ac=
tion=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D37b4a7c7452bb702b31cfe5f7310fc9a018=
075f067de2ba7857d4c0c59c4a9e6&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&a=
mp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D08996cc4bcbf=
002f99b996069f462670&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfi=
ne.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvSGlzdG9yeV9=
vZl93cml0aW5n&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"col=
or: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">invented</a> a clever three-step =
algorithm for encrypting messages. In step one, the user takes a message an=
d decomposes it into a set of distinct sounds. In step two, the user encryp=
ts these sounds into a set of visual symbols. And in step three, the user p=
reserves these symbols on a physical medium.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">The purpose of this en=
cryption technology is to transmit meaning across time and space. When anot=
her user encounters the encrypted message, they decrypt it by employing the=
 same algorithm in reverse. First, they parse the symbols and convert them =
into sounds. Next, they parse these sounds and group them into chunks of me=
aning. Finally, they interpret the decoded message.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">With this ancient tech=
nology in mind, here is how our story unfolds. For centuries after its inve=
ntion, the encryption algorithm was used by a small class of administrators=
 who hoarded its secrets. Then, about three hundred years ago, the decrypti=
on keys were <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.c=
om?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D6bfdb8c06b4ff4d9398ac46fd7f07c=
9c92fc0e718c07c817eceedbe1ff737ece&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14=
975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D569c5f4=
75faa4ea8fb349ed1f20a3021&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@w=
oodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9vdXJ3b3JsZGluZGF0YS5vcmcvbGl0ZXJhY3=
k&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9;=
 text-decoration: underline;">gradually released</a> to the wider populatio=
n. Eventually, all children received <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://e=
conomicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D62ceed=
1eef66fec9181677290ede48b6d8e3cdbdf8f1bfbe0f52400e6115a4fe&amp;blog_id=3D16=
0901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508=
&amp;signature=3D56810db2b3f8070943f32a2abb30170a&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post=
&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcG=
VkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvQ29tcHVsc29yeV9lZHVjYXRpb24&amp;email_id=3D2ccc0182904982=
54a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">m=
andatory decryption training</a>.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">But then a funny thing=
 happened. After several generations of formal training, some users began t=
o feel that the decryption algorithm was =E2=80=98natural=E2=80=99, and tha=
t its intricacies need not be taught. These users created a <a target=3D"_b=
lank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_red=
irect&amp;uuid=3D855efab8175a4bb405ac679a5c3fe72285a5be0104ae2fe64c1e6c9085=
fdde5d&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&=
amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3Dd5512f4b3ed2c104fd5465d5e65db9c3&am=
p;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=
=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvV2hvbGVfbGFuZ3VhZ2U&amp;email_id=
=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decorati=
on: underline;">new approach to training</a> whereby the decryption algorit=
hm was learned through exposure. New users were shown encrypted messages wi=
th convenient pictures and cues that elucidated the meaning. The idea was t=
hat through repeated exposure, new users would master the technology.</p>=
=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Or not.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">After several decades =
of this new learning regime, scientists found that decryption skills were i=
n decline, and that the drop was biggest among the weakest decrypters. Mean=
while, new communication technology had proliferated, leading to confusion =
about the loss of decryption skill. Was the new technology to blame? Or was=
 it something else? Opinions flared, but conclusive evidence was in short s=
upply.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;"><img src=3D"https://ec=
onomicsfromthetopdown.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/divider.png" width=3D"=
120" style=3D"border: none; -ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; max-width: 100=
%; margin-bottom: 24px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: au=
to;"></p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Exiting our parable, l=
et=E2=80=99s take stock. In English, the act of encrypting a message is cal=
led <em>writing</em>. And the act of decrypting it is called <em>reading</e=
m>. Both acts rely on an implicit algorithm for decomposing linguistic mean=
ing into sounds, and encoding these sounds into symbols. Good readers have =
mastered this algorithm. Bad readers have not. And today, bad readers have =
not mastered this algorithm largely because they were not taught how it wor=
ks. Or at least, that is my contention here.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">The backstory is that =
in the 1980s and 1990s, a movement called the <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"=
https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=
=3D855efab8175a4bb405ac679a5c3fe72285a5be0104ae2fe64c1e6c9085fdde5d&amp;blo=
g_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D=
754610508&amp;signature=3Dd5512f4b3ed2c104fd5465d5e65db9c3&amp;email_name=
=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9=
lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvV2hvbGVfbGFuZ3VhZ2U&amp;email_id=3D2ccc0182904=
98254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;=
">=E2=80=98whole language=E2=80=99</a> approach to reading swept through an=
glophone schools. According to this new zeitgeist, learning to read was as =
=E2=80=98natural=E2=80=99 as learning to speak. It was a skill that could b=
e learned largely by exposure. Soon this method of <a target=3D"_blank" hre=
f=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp=
;uuid=3Dc44635fe213cbaafefcb362e0b6d6e79a40ed9c1d525709d04fb1ac44cb7a6bb&am=
p;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_=
id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D0fdb2179dff7ee098ffe87a6a74fc369&amp;email_n=
ame=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cubmV3eW9ya2VyLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FubmFscy1vZi1lZHVjYXRpb24vdGhlLXJpc2UtYW5=
kLWZhbGwtb2YtdmliZXMtYmFzZWQtbGl0ZXJhY3k&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f=
7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">=E2=80=
=98vibe-based literacy=E2=80=99</a> came to dominate elementary-school peda=
gogy, with devastating results. Yes, some students flourished. But a large =
portion of kids were simply left behind, destined to be perpetually poor re=
aders. Today, we are living with the consequences.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In this essay, I make =
the case that the modern decline of high-school reading ability is in large=
 part, due to the spread of whole-language methods. I will build my case in=
 three parts.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In Part I, I review ho=
w reading scores have declined among US high-school students. I show how th=
is decline is not uniform, but is instead marked by a widening skill gap. A=
mong US high-school students, the best readers have actually gotten better =
over time, but the worst readers have gotten far worse. Importantly, this r=
eading-score gap remains visible across a variety of student demographics. =
Which is to say that whatever is causing the widening gap, it=E2=80=99s not=
 something that government surveys measure.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In Part II, I take a d=
etour into the history of how writing was invented. My purpose is to illust=
rate exactly why reading is hard to learn, and why students benefit when th=
e requisite skills are explicitly taught. Then I discuss the whole-language=
 movement to <em>not</em> teach these skills =E2=80=94 a movement based on =
a misguided view of what it means to read.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In Part III, I build t=
he case that whole-language instruction is the main cause of the widening r=
eading-score gap. I survey many lines of evidence, perhaps the most importa=
nt of which is that the reading-score gap can be reversed =E2=80=A6 by aban=
doning whole-language methods and teaching structured literacy.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Of course, my goal her=
e is not to exonerate smartphones and other screen devices from wasting kid=
s=E2=80=99 time. Instead, my point is that if we don=E2=80=99t properly tea=
ch kids <em>how</em> to read, they have little chance of actually doing it.=
</p>=0A=
