7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">For early writers, the=
 hurdle was to somehow use pictures to encode messages that went beyond one=
-word statements like =E2=80=98bull=E2=80=99 or =E2=80=98snake=E2=80=99. Fo=
r example, how would you use pictures to write this sentence?</p>=0A=
<blockquote style=3D"background: #f6f7f7; margin: 0; border-left: 4px solid=
 #3858e9; padding: 24px; font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsyste=
mfont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvet=
ica Neue&quot;,sans-serif; font-style: normal;">=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.7; padding: 0; co=
