<h4 id=3D"a-decoding-deficit-creates-a-compound-reading-failure" style=3D"c=
olor: #2d3338; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin:=
 48px 0 24px; letter-spacing: -.02em; text-transform: uppercase;">5. A deco=
ding deficit creates a compound reading failure</h4>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">The fifth piece of evi=
dence implicating whole-language methods in the widening reading-score gap =
is the fact that by downplaying decoding skills (and encouraging students t=
o guess at words), the approach likely creates a compound reading failure.<=
/p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">To understand this eff=
ect, realize that reading comprehension is the product of two distinct skil=
ls. Reading comprehension depends firstly on the <em>ability to decode word=
s</em>. And it depends secondly on <em>oral comprehension</em>. According t=
o the <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?acti=
on=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3Dc71503b0767adba0cc791fe698113b5a27045=
09495d7003000e80bb9efca4ef3&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp=
;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3Dc114c1c0eb4292=
4f24c4598db4221cc5&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine=
.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvU2ltcGxlX3ZpZ=
Xdfb2ZfcmVhZGluZw=3D&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=
=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">=E2=80=98simple view of re=
ading=E2=80=99</a>, reading comprehension is the product of these two abili=
ties:</p>=0A=
<div style=3D"margin-bottom: 24px; text-align: center;">=0A=
</div>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Now in principle, deco=
ding skill is separate from oral comprehension, which is why someone can be=
 fluent but illiterate. That said, in literate cultures, oral comprehension=
 tends to be a function of decoding ability itself. And that=E2=80=99s beca=
use writing is the most potent source of knowledge.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Simply by reading, a g=
ood decoder can learn about new words and new ideas, causing their oral com=
prehension to grow with time. In contrast, a poor decoder struggles to unlo=
ck the knowledge contained within books, which means that their oral compre=
hension remains stunted. But here is the kicker. Because reading comprehens=
ion depends on the <em>product</em> of decoding and oral abilities, poor de=
coders suffer a compound failure. Their poor decoding hinders their oral co=
mprehension, and so their reading comprehension suffers doubly.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Figure&nbsp;<a href=3D=
"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uui=
d=3D76e075817b08718d4322aad07727ab70b19e07d2bcac54a5f349ce5560403d21&amp;bl=
og_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=
