mVjdA=3D&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #=
3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">longitudinal study</a> of 485 students=
 in Iowa and Illinois, whose school progress was tracked throughout 1990s. =
The chart illustrates how students=E2=80=99 vocabulary depended on their de=
coding skills, which were measured in grade 4. (Vocabulary is a crude proxy=
