=3D&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e=
9; text-decoration: underline;">=E2=80=98Mississippi miracle=E2=80=99</a> =
=E2=80=94 the fact that it targeted the worst readers and helped them the m=
ost. Mississippi=E2=80=99s experiment strongly suggests that the widening s=
kill gap between the best and worst high-school readers is not inevitable, =
and that it=E2=80=99s been driven by whole-language pedagogy =E2=80=94 a te=
aching approach that systematically fails the worst readers.</p>=0A=
<h3 id=3D"when-the-method-creates-the-disease" style=3D"color: #2d3338; lin=
e-height: 1.2; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin: 48px 0 24px;">Whe=
n the method creates the disease</h3>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">When parents send thei=
r kids to school, they no doubt assume that the teacher uses the best metho=
ds for instruction, much as a patient assumes that their doctor uses the be=
st forms of medicine. Unfortunately, if the history of science tells us any=
thing, it is that best practices are not guaranteed.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">The problem is that on=
ce a flawed practice becomes institutionalized, it is difficult for the pra=
ctitioner to discern that their method is unsound. If you practice only wha=
t your mentor preached (and you=E2=80=99re surrounded by others who do the =
same), the failure of your method becomes invisible. Which is why doctors p=
racticed bloodletting for centuries, yet were oblivious to the fact that it=
 tended to kill their patients.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">It=E2=80=99s within th=
is context that we should interpret the whole-language movement. It promote=
d a flawed teaching method that, once institutionalized, became invisible t=
o its practitioners. When children <em>did</em> learn to read (despite thei=
r poor instruction), it was proof that the method worked. And if the child =
failed, they were just =E2=80=98slow learners=E2=80=99 who=E2=80=99d eventu=
ally get the gist of reading. In short, it was the <em>method</em> that suc=
ceeded, but the individual <em>child</em> who failed.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Still, there=E2=80=99s=
 the question of how such a flawed practice managed to become a tradition. =
Did whole-language teaching become popular because it contained a kernel of=
 truth? I think the answer is no. The whole-language approach became popula=
r because it <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.c=
om?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D12123f31e852b5e48255136693fd8b=
1939ec06ef6ebd959e3e3bf2e933b80f2c&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14=
975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D5af0716=
3a82941f9b1476d8660f4e9ca&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@w=
oodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9mZWF0dXJlcy5hcG1yZXBvcnRzLm9yZy9zb2=
xkLWEtc3Rvcnkv&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"co=
lor: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">told a story</a> that people wan=
ted to hear. Whole-language theory sold the idea that learning to read is a=
s natural as learning to speak. The message, then, is that the teacher can =
empower their students largely by <em>getting out of the way</em>. So forge=
t lectures. Forget drills. Forget explicit instruction. Just give kids a ch=
ance to explore great literature, and they will naturally learn how to read=
.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">To grasp the appeal of=
 this idea, we must understand the context in which it emerged. Prior to th=
e 1960s, anglophone schooling was a dictatorial affair. It was a place wher=
e the teacher was a sergeant and the kids were compliant enlistees. It was =
an environment that did not exactly stimulate high-minded thinking. It was =
this dictatorial environment that whole-language proponents rejected. They =
sold (and <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?=
action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3Dd7a7604457f00fde980699d5998b91e2d=
345c1435f45e4150568fefcddea9e81&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975=
&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D2660cfdbe4=
d414c0dc606033c62dddaa&amp;email_name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@wood=
fine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFuZGZvbmxpbmUuY29tL2RvaS9mdWxsL=
zEwLjExMTEvZWllLjEyMDk2&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" st=
yle=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underline;">still sell</a>) their a=
pproach as a =E2=80=9Cdemocratic=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Chumanistic=E2=80=9D =
method that empowers =E2=80=9Cteachers and students alike=E2=80=9D. In shor=
t, the spread of whole-language teaching had more to do with political idea=
ls than with any evidence that the method was sound.<a target=3D"_blank" hr=
ef=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&am=
p;uuid=3D917df91375f66ebd28359e42904b614bdff6637bfcba81f7a51746f91aaf5780&a=
mp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs=
_id=3D754610508&amp;signature=3D5acd968b4e4b96a255bcb0fe03f9ebf8&amp;email_=
name=3Dnew-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM=
6Ly9lY29ub21pY3Nmcm9tdGhldG9wZG93bi5jb20vMjAyNi8wMy8yOC93aHkta2lkcy1hcmUtZ2=
V0dGluZy13b3JzZS1hdC1yZWFkaW5nLXRoZS1jYXNlLWFnYWluc3Qtd2hvbGUtbGFuZ3VhZ2Utd=
GVhY2hpbmcvI2ZuOA=3D&amp;email_id=3D2ccc018290498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" class=
=3D"footnote-ref" id=3D"fnref8" role=3D"doc-noteref" style=3D"color: #3858e=
9; text-decoration: underline;"><sup>8</sup></a></p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Now, the irony is that=
 although whole-language methods were billed as a tool for empowering <em>a=
ll</em> children, what they actually did was to empower the <em>best</em> s=
tudents =E2=80=94 the kids who learned to read effortlessly, and who benefi=
ted from have time (and resources) to practice their skills. But for the ki=
ds who struggled to decode words, the whole-language environment was downri=
ght confusing, since they were being asked to =E2=80=98practice=E2=80=99 a =
task that they found bewildering. It was the equivalent of giving a ten-yea=
r old integral calculus and saying =E2=80=9CDo the math, kid. I=E2=80=99m e=
mpowering you by not teaching you how it works.=E2=80=9D</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Of course, the failure=
 of whole-language methods doesn=E2=80=99t mean that wrote dictatorial teac=
hing is the way to go. It is not. The real message is that higher-level abi=
lities do not come from the ether; they depend on the mastery of lower-leve=
l skills.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Great jazz musicians i=
mprovise effortlessly because they=E2=80=99ve internalized low-level skills=
 like scales and chord progressions. Great mathematicians produced abstract=
 proofs because they=E2=80=99ve mastered the low-level skills behind arithm=
etic and algebra. Great writers produce compelling literature because they=
=E2=80=99ve been taught the low-level mechanics of their language. And good=
 readers can parse text accurately and rapidly because they grasp the low-l=
evel algorithm of how symbols encode linguistic sounds.</p>=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">In each case, choosing=
 to <em>not</em> teach these low-level skills isn=E2=80=99t =E2=80=98democr=
atic=E2=80=99. It isn=E2=80=99t =E2=80=98humanistic=E2=80=99. It is the def=
inition of <em>regressive</em>. Choosing to not teach low-level skills is a=
 recipe for selecting the least gifted students and systematically leaving =
them behind. It is a recipe for producing the outcomes we now observe =E2=
=80=A6 a widening gap between the best readers and the worst readers.</p>=
=0A=
<p style=3D"font-family: -apple-system,system-ui,blinkmacsystemfont,&quot;S=
egoe UI&quot;,Roboto,Oxygen-Sans,Ubuntu,Cantarell,&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot=
;,sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; margin: 0; line-height: 1.=
7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-bottom: 24px;">Of course, the evidenc=
e against whole-language teaching does not get smartphones and algorithmic =
slop off the hook for polluting our social environment. But then again, whe=
n kids struggle to merely decode words, they have little reason to get off =
their phones and actually read.</p>=0A=
