.7; padding: 0; color: #101517; margin-left: 8px; margin-top: 24px;">How I =
came to (briefly) believe in whole-language teaching is a somewhat embarras=
sing case study in how bad science spreads. When my daughter was around the=
 age of four, the topic of reading instruction was on my mind. As luck woul=
d have it, one day when I was substitute teaching at Leaside High School in=
 Toronto, I was sitting in the staffroom and came upon a dusty book on read=
ing instruction. Now, I have no recollection of the name of the book or its=
 author. But it could have plausibly been <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"http=
s://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duser_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D0=
79faeebaeff17ce1485fb96b367c3adfdcee41f9adb40e2cc01a99d64faf75d&amp;blog_id=
=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=3D259268523&amp;subs_id=3D7546=
10508&amp;signature=3D142e981f137b4b368a4b4597dab5661c&amp;email_name=3Dnew=
-post&amp;user_email=3Dinfo@woodfine.co&amp;encoded_url=3DaHR0cHM6Ly9hcmNoa=
XZlLm9yZy9kZXRhaWxzL3JlYWRpbmd3aXRob3V0bm8wMHNtaXQ&amp;email_id=3D2ccc01829=
0498254a8f7ab6d227747ea" style=3D"color: #3858e9; text-decoration: underlin=
e;"><em>Reading Without Nonsense</em></a>, written by the psycholinguist <a=
 target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://economicsfromthetopdown.com?action=3Duse=
r_content_redirect&amp;uuid=3D2c626893c8bb02ee5b39b66162f6e0e79592f2b12eb4c=
792a3c38b97b3d3f62b&amp;blog_id=3D160901125&amp;post_id=3D14975&amp;user_id=
